# Customer Purchase Prediction using K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

This project demonstrates how to build a **K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) classification model** and deploy it using **Streamlit** to predict whether a customer will purchase a product.

The project follows a complete machine learning workflow including data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment.

---

## Technologies & Libraries Used

- Python
- NumPy
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn
- Streamlit
- Pickle

---

## Dataset Description

The dataset contains customer information with the following columns:

- User ID
- Gender
- Age
- Estimated Salary
- Purchased (Target Variable)

Features used for training:

- Age
- Estimated Salary

Target variable:

- Purchased (0 = No, 1 = Yes)

---

## Project Workflow

### 1. Data Loading

The dataset is loaded using Pandas and split into features (X) and target variable (y).

---

### 2. Train-Test Split

The dataset is divided into:

- 80% training data
- 20% testing data

This helps evaluate the model on unseen data.

---

### 3. Feature Scaling

StandardScaler is applied to normalize feature values so that distance calculations used by KNN are not biased.

---

### 4. Model Training

A **K-Nearest Neighbors classifier** is trained with the following parameters:

- n_neighbors = 5
- weights = distance
- p = 2 (Euclidean distance)

The model learns patterns from the training dataset.

---

### 5. Model Evaluation

The trained model is evaluated using multiple metrics:

- Confusion Matrix
- Accuracy Score
- Precision
- Recall
- F1-score
- ROC Curve
- ROC-AUC Score

The ROC curve helps visualize the classification performance.

---

### 6. Model Saving

The trained model and scaler are saved using **pickle**:

- knn_model.pkl
- scaler.pkl

This allows the model to be reused in the deployment application.

---

## Streamlit Application

An interactive Streamlit web app is created to allow users to make predictions.

### Features

- Upload CSV dataset
- Generate predictions automatically
- View prediction results
- ROC curve visualization
- Download predicted results

---

